>  I got a new Bosal Catalytic converter. It has the triangle flange on one 
> side and the coupling on the other side. Generally, the triangle flange 
> goes to the Y-pipe (inlet) and the coupling goes to the muffler (outlet). 
> However, this cat. has an arrow on the outside baffle signifying the flow 
> should go from the coupling side to the triangle flange side, reverse of 
> how it should be.  This makes it impossible to install, without cutting 
> and welding.
